# Hostinger: set env vars for your containers
# ------------------------------------------
# Option A: Create a file named .env on your Hostinger server in the SAME folder
#           as your docker-compose file. Paste the variables below and fill in values.
#           Then run: docker compose up -d
#
# Option B: In Hostinger Docker / Compose UI, add these as "Environment variables"
#           for your stack (if the UI supports it).
#
# Replace YOUR_VPS_IP with your actual IP (e.g. 72.61.74.168) or your domain.

# ========== FOR API + POSTGRES STACK (docker-compose with api service) ==========

# --- Required for API CORS: frontend URL. No trailing slash. ---
WEB_APP_URL=http://YOUR_VPS_IP:3000

# --- If you use API + Postgres compose (with-db, full, with-db-pull) ---
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your-secure-postgres-password

# --- API secrets (if you use Stream Chat, JWT, etc.) ---
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret
# STREAM_API_KEY=
# STREAM_API_SECRET=

# ========== FOR WEB (FRONTEND) STACK (docker-compose.hostinger-web-only.yml) ==========
# Use these in the .env (or Hostinger env UI) for the server where the WEB container runs.

# --- Required: NextAuth. Where users open the app. No trailing slash. ---
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://YOUR_VPS_IP:3000
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-nextauth-secret

# --- Required for email/password login: API URL so the web server can call the API. No trailing slash. ---
API_URL=http://YOUR_VPS_IP:3002

# --- Optional: Google OAuth (only if you use "Sign in with Google") ---
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# NOTE: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_STREAM_API_KEY are baked into the image at BUILD time (GitHub).
# They are baked into the web image at BUILD time. Set them in GitHub:
#   Repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables
#   - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL = http://YOUR_VPS_IP:3002  (your API URL)
#   - NEXT_PUBLIC_STREAM_API_KEY = (your Stream key, if using Stream Chat)
# Then re-run "Build and push Web image" workflow so the new image has the correct API URL.
